Description: Laureate bust of Antoninus Pius, undraped, right. (obverse)

Dioscuri standing front looking at each other; each wears short chiton & chlamys, & rests outer hand on spear (point downwards), inner hand holding parazonium; between them, crescent with horns. (reverse)
